There are two data frames needed - saved in your `{{< meta practical >}}/data`  directory as `data/breeding_site_locations.csv` and `data/migratory_connectivity_dataset.csv`.

::: {.callout-exercise #ex-read_csv}

{{< fa solid anchor >}}

In your **worked example** Quarto document, read `data/breeding_site_locations.csv` into a variable, then view it with `gt`.

::: {.callout-note #note-read_csv}
Reminder: The R function `read_csv` reads a CSV file into R as a data frame. The function `gt` is used to view a data frame.
:::

::: {.callout-answer collapse="true" #ex-read_csv_ans}

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
bird_breeding_sites <- read_csv("data/breeding_site_locations.csv")
gt(bird_breeding_sites)
